# React App — `apps/web`

The web app lets users connect to a Sisense instance, select dashboards/widgets, run wellcheck analysis, and view results.

## Stack

- **Vite** React, TypeScript
- **SDK** consumed from `packages/sdk` — never call Sisense API directly from app code
- UI components from `packages/ui`

## Key Pages / Features

| Route | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `/` | Connection setup (base URL + API token) |
| `/dashboards` | List and select dashboards |
| `/dashboards/[id]` | List widgets, trigger analysis |
| `/dashboards/[id]/results` | Show ESLint wellcheck results per widget |

## Displaying Results

Each wellcheck violation should show:
- Rule name (`no-metadata-override-in-script`)
- Severity (`error` | `warning`)
- Line number and relevant code snippet
- A short human-readable description of the problem
